{\tc\tcl2 \v Part 1 \'96 OOP Refactoring ({\f2 balancer_t} )}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPA}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPA}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
Goal of the refactoring
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v Goal of the refactoring}
The pre-existing {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 main.c}}}}  mixed multiple concerns in one file: hardware instantiation, peripheral init, mode/state machine, control law, and parameter editing. Adding distance control on top of that flat structure would have made the code even more overloaded. The refactoring introduces one {\i object}  that holds all subsystems, exposes a small set of public method-pointers, and keeps {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 main.c}}}}  focused on scheduling.\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPB}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPB}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
The C-with-structs OOP pattern
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v The C-with-structs OOP pattern}
{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "https://www.state-machine.com/oop" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Quantum Leaps' guide}}} can be a good starting point to understanding and applying the use of object oriented programming in C. In the following it will be exlpained to what extend and how those conceps have been incorporated into the balancer refactoring.\par
The pattern follows the convention already used by {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PIDContr_t}}}}  in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAAZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 regler.h}}}}  and the hardware drivers: a struct stores both data fields and {\b function pointers as members} . The pointer assignments are made once, at file scope, in a single {\f2 const}  {\i prototype instance} :\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* in balancer_t.c - the prototype instance */}\par
{\cf17 const} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
 = \{\par
    .init               = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerInit}}}
,\par
    .updatePitch        = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch}}}
,\par
    .updateDist         = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist}}}
,\par
    .updateDisplay      = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDR" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDisplay}}}
,\par
    .DispAlphaNumMPU    = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDN" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerDispAlphaNumMPU}}}
,\par
    .paramEdit          = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDT" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerParamEdit}}}
,\par
\};\par
}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab {\b Encapsulation:}  A class is a struct of attributes plus functions that take {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}} *b}  as first argument; a {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAER" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerCreate()}}}}  initialises the instance; method implementations live in the .c file \u8594? {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAAV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 balancer_t.h}}}}  declares, {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAATX" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 balancer_t.c}}}}  defines.\par}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* Attributes \'97 balancer_t.h */}\par
{\cf17 struct }{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
 \{\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACN" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050_t}}}
   *{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACO" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pIMU}}}
;\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 TOFSensor_t}}}
 *{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pTOF}}}
;\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PIDContr_t}}}
   {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PID_phi}}}
;\par
    {\cf20 /* ...state, params, timers... */}\par
\};\par
\par
{\cf20 /* Operations \'97 balancer_t.c, all static (file-private) */}\par
{\cf17 static} {\cf18 void} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerInit}}}
       ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b) \{ ... \}\par
{\cf17 static} {\cf18 void} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch}}}
({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b) \{ ... \}\par
{\cf17 static} {\cf18 void} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist}}}
 ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b) \{ ... \}\par
\par
{\cf20 /* Constructor */}\par
{\cf18 void} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAER" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerCreate}}}
({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b, {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACN" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050_t}}}
 *imu, {\cf20 /* ... */}) \{\par
    *b = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
;\par
    b->{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACO" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pIMU}}}
 = imu;\par
    {\cf20 /* ... */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
.{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 init}}}
(b);\par
\}\par
}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab {\b Inheritance:}  Not used in this project \'96 {\f2 balancer_t}  has no {\b super}  member anywhere. It expresses relationships via composition and aggregation (see {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABOW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 class diagram}}}).\par}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* balancer_t.h \'97 Balancer "has a" IMU, "has a" pitch PID */}\par
{\cf17 struct }{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
 \{\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACN" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050_t}}}
   *{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACO" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pIMU}}}
;       {\cf20 /* aggregation: pointer, lifetime external */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 TOFSensor_t}}}
 *{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pTOF}}}
;       {\cf20 /* aggregation */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACR" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Stepper_t}}}
   *{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACS" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pStepL}}}
;     {\cf20 /* aggregation */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PIDContr_t}}}
   {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PID_phi}}}
;    {\cf20 /* composition: owned by value */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PIDContr_t}}}
   {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACX" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PID_dist}}}
;   {\cf20 /* composition */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MeanVal_t}}}
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADA" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 LPF_dist}}}
;   {\cf20 /* composition */}\par
    {\cf20 /* ... */}\par
\};\par
}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab {\b Polymorphism:}  The function pointers live directly inside the instance struct.\par}
\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* balancer_t.h */}\par
{\cf17 struct }{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
 \{\par
    {\cf20 /* ...attributes... */}\par
    void (*{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 init}}}
)         ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b);\par
    void (*{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 updatePitch}}}
)  ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b);\par
    void (*{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEN" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 updateDist}}}
)   ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b);\par
    void (*{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEO" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 updateDisplay}}}
)({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b);\par
    void (*{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 paramEdit}}}
)    ({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b);\par
\};\par
{\cf17 extern} {\cf17 const} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
;    {\cf20 /* prototype object */}\par
}
\par
The pointers are seeded from a single const prototype, copied wholesale into each instance by the constructor:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* balancer_t.c */}\par
{\cf17 const} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
 = \{\par
    .init          = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerInit}}}
,\par
    .updatePitch   = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch}}}
,\par
    .updateDist    = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist}}}
,\par
    .updateDisplay = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDR" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDisplay}}}
,\par
    .paramEdit     = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDT" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerParamEdit}}}
,\par
\};\par
\par
{\cf18 void} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAER" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerCreate}}}
({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}
 *b, {\cf20 /* ...HW ptrs... */}) \{\par
    *b = {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
;            {\cf20 /* <== copy prototype, including method ptrs */}\par
    b->{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACO" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pIMU}}}
 = imu;\par
    {\cf20 /* ... */}\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}}
.{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAEL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 init}}}
(b);\par
\};\par
}
\par
Calls then use the instance's own copy of the pointer \'96 {\f2 bala.updatePitch(&{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}})}  in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 main.c}}}} .\par
The actual method implementations are {\f2 static}  (file-private), so the only public entry points are the function pointers carried by the struct itself.\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPC}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPC}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
What {\f2 Balancer_t}  aggregates
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v What {\f2 Balancer_t}  aggregates}
{\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}}  (defined in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAAV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 balancer_t.h}}}} ) groups its fields by responsibility, exactly as visualised in the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABOW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 class diagram}}}:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain {\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\afs24\lang1081\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af3\dbch\af3\loch\f8 \'01\u8226\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi-360\tx360\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\kerning1\hich\af4\dbch\af5\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs20
{\b HW pointers}  \'96 {\f2 *pIMU} , {\f2 *pTOF} , {\f2 *pStepL} , {\f2 *pStepR} , {\f2 *pBatADC} . The hardware objects themselves are {\f2 static}  globals in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 main.c}}}} ; their addresses are {\i injected}  via {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAER" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerCreate()}}}} . This is dependency injection, not ownership.\par
