\par
The output of the cascade is {\f2 b->pitchOffset} . Inside the existing {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch()}}}} , it is added to the pitch reference and clamped by {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_pClamp}}}}  so that the outer loops can never destabilise the inner one:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf20 /* inside BalancerUpdatePitch() */}\par
{\cf18 float} offset = b->{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 pitchOffset}}}
;\par
{\cf19 if} (offset >  pClamp) offset =  pClamp;\par
{\cf19 if} (offset < -pClamp) offset = -pClamp;\par
{\cf18 float} error_phi = pitch - offset;\par
{\cf18 float} setPitch  = (float){\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDX" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 rad2step}}}
 * {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAOL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PID}}}
.run(&b->{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PID_phi}}}
, error_phi);\par
}
\par
This is the single integration point between the two halves of the project: {\f2 pitchOffset}  is written by {\f2 updateDist()}  and read by {\f2 updatePitch()} . Everything else stays decoupled.\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPJ}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPJ}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
TOF handling and velocity fusion
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v TOF handling and velocity fusion}
{\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist()}}}}  (in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAATX" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 balancer_t.c}}}} ) executes the outer two loops. Two practical details are worth highlighting:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab {\b TOF dropouts.}  When the sensor returns {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAYU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 TOF_VL53L0X_OUT_OF_RANGE}}}}  or a value below {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACD" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_distBlind}}}} , the controller freezes the last filtered distance, sets {\f2 distanceVelo = 0} , and clears the velocity-PID integral. This avoids spikes from blind-spot readings driving the robot off.\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
2.\tab {\b Velocity measurement.}  Two independent estimates exist: {\f2 distanceVelo}  derived from the filtered TOF, and {\f2 translationVeloMean}  derived from stepper-position differences ({\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 STEP_TO_MM_S}}}}  conversion, mean of left and right wheel). The current implementation picks whichever has the larger magnitude as {\f2 veloMeas}  \'96 a simple "trust whichever shows movement" heuristic. This is a candidate for a proper sensor-fusion later.\par}
\par
\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPK}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPK}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
New parameters
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v New parameters}
The {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACK" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 ParamIdx}}}}  enum and {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 defaultParam}}}[]}  are extended with the cascade tunables \'96 every value is editable live via the rotary encoder + push button ({\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDT" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerParamEdit()}}}} ):\par
{\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dKP}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dKI}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACA" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dKD}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dSP}}}}  (setpoint mm), {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACC" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dLPF}}}}  (TOF {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAOB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MeanVal}}} weight), {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACD" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_distBlind}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACE" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_vKP}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACF" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_vKI}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACG" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_vKD}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACH" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_vMax}}}} , {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACI" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_a2p}}}}  (acceleration\u8594?pitch gain), {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_pClamp}}}} .\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPL}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPL}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
Mode integration in {\f2 main.c} 
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v Mode integration in {\f2 main.c} }
The new mode {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DistCtrl}}}}  runs the inner pitch loop on every {\f2 StepTask}  tick (7 ms) and the outer/middle loops only when {\f2 DistCtrlTaskTimer}  expires (49 ms):\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid {\cf19 case} {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DistCtrl}}}
:\par
    {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
.updatePitch(&{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
);                         {\cf20 /* every 7 ms */}\par
    {\cf19 if} (isSystickExpired({\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
.DistCtrlTaskTimer)) \{\par
        systickSetTicktime(&{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
.DistCtrlTaskTimer, {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 DistCtrlTaskTimeMs}}}
);\par
        {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
.updateDist(&{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 bala}}}
);                      {\cf20 /* every 49 ms */}\par
    \}\par
    {\cf19 break};\par
}
\par
{\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABI" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_Bala}}}}  is unchanged \'96 it simply does not call {\f2 updateDist()} , so {\f2 pitchOffset}  stays zero and the inner loop behaves exactly as before. This makes {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABI" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_Bala}}}}  the safe fallback during distance-loop tuning.\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABPM}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABPM}
