{\tc\tcl2 \v Diagrams}
The three diagrams referenced from the sections above sit alongside this page in the Doxygen output.\par
{\b Class diagram \'96 {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}}  aggregate}  {\i (Part 1)}  Shows the root aggregate {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}}}  with its six sub-sections (HW pointers, control objects, operating state, parameters, SysTick timers, method-pointers). HW instances live in {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAASJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 main.c}}}}  and are aggregated by pointer; PIDs and the LPF are owned by value (composition). The diagram colour-codes what is new (distance-control fields and methods) versus what existed.\par
{\b Program schedule \'96 {\f2 TaskMode}  FSM and tick scheduling}  {\i (Part 1 \u8594? Part 2 entry point)}  Shows the mode transitions ({\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABC" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_InitBat}}}}  \u8594? {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABF" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_CheckI2cSlaves}}}}  \u8594? {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABI" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_Bala}}} / {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABD" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DispMpuData}}} / {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABE" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DispTofData}}} / {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DistCtrl}}}} ) driven by the rotary parameter {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_MODE}}}} , and how the three SysTick timers ({\f2 StepTaskTimer}  7 ms, {\f2 DistCtrlTaskTimer}  49 ms, {\f2 DispTaskTimer}  700 ms) trigger which methods inside the main loop.\par
{\b Cascaded control loops \'96 {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAABJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 M_DistCtrl}}}} }  {\i (Part 2)}  Signal-flow diagram of the three nested loops. From left to right: distance setpoint {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_dSP}}}}  \u8594? outer PID \u8594? {\f2 tarVelo}  (clamped by {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACH" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_vMax}}}} ) \u8594? middle PID \u8594? target acceleration \u8594? {\f2 * {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACI" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_a2p}}}}  \u8594? {\f2 pitchOffset}  (clamped by {\f2 {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 a_pClamp}}}} ) \u8594? inner pitch PID \u8594? stepper command. Sensor returns: TOF + {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAOB" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MeanVal}}} LPF for distance, stepper-position derivative + TOF derivative for velocity (selected by max-magnitude switch).\par
