{\row }
}
{
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab The function sends the value of {\f2 sensor->LPFiltConfig}  to the {\b CONFIG}  register of the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAHZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050}}} using I2C communication.\par
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
2.\tab The low-pass filter setting controls the cutoff frequency for gyroscope and accelerometer signals, as defined by the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAHZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050}}} datasheet.\par
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
3.\tab The user must set the desired filter configuration value in the {\f2 LPFiltConfig}  field of the {\f2 sensor}  structure before calling this function.\par}
