Detailed Description\par
\pard\plain 
{
\pard\plain \s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid {\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
: This library file handles communication with a Time-of-Flight (TOF) sensor. Currently adapted to the VL53LOX sensor. The library supports both single-shot and continuous measurement modes. Configuration is managed via the appropriate register settings for the sensor. \par
}{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
\par
{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Authors\par}\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\s17 \sa60 \sb30
: Linus Blanke & Christoph Lederbogen & Andreas Ladner & Philipp R\'F6hlke \par
: tflaemig68 \par
}}{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Date\par}\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\s17 \sa60 \sb30
: April 2025 \par
: July 2025 updates by tflaemig68 marked with //!< TF_July25\par
}}This code and the register addresses are based on the official API, which can be found here: {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "https://www.st.com/en/embedded-software/stsw-img005.html#get-software" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 https://www.st.com/en/embedded-software/stsw-img005.html#get-software}}}
