\pard\plain \s61\li360\sa60\sb30\qj\widctlpar\qj\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
\par
{
{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
: Configures the SPAD (Single Photon Avalanche Diode) settings for the Time-of-Flight (TOF) sensor. }}\par
{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
@function: TOF_set_spads_from_nvm\par
: This function reads SPAD configuration data from the sensor's non-volatile memory (NVM) and sets up the SPAD array for operation. It retrieves the SPAD count and type (aperture or non-aperture) using the TOF_get_spad_info_from_nvm function. Based on this data, the function adjusts the SPAD enable map stored in the sensor's memory to activate the appropriate SPADs. This ensures the sensor operates optimally according to its hardware configuration.\par
