}The corresponding sample times in seconds are provided by TA_INNER and TA_OUTER and are used when initializing the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 PIDContr_t}}} objects.\par
{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Cascade integration\par
}\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid The distance-control extension is coupled into the original pitch-control loop through b->pitchOffset. {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist()}}} computes this value from the outer distance loop and the middle velocity loop. {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch()}}} then subtracts the clamped pitch offset from the measured pitch before the inner PID_phi controller is evaluated.\par
}In M_Bala, {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDist()}}} is not executed, so the pitch controller behaves as the original balancing loop. When the selected mode is not M_DistCtrl, {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDR" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdateDisplay()}}} resets the distance-control state, including pitchOffset and tarVelo, to avoid reusing stale outer-loop values.\par
If a fall is detected in {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDP" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerUpdatePitch()}}}, the distance and velocity controller states are additionally reset so that accumulated outer-loop integrator values do not remain active after recovery.\par
{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Visibility\par
}\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid Functions that are only used inside this translation unit are declared static. The public {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACM" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer_t}}} interface is provided through {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAAV" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 balancer_t.h}}}. The main public construction entry point is {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 BalancerCreate()}}}; the method pointers themselves are initialized from the const {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAACL" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Balancer}}} prototype.\par
}{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Attention\par}\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\s17 \sa60 \sb30
