{\xe \v rad2step\:balancer_t.c}
{\xe \v balancer_t.c\:rad2step}
\pard\plain \s4\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs20\cgrid {
{\b 
const int16_t rad2step = 520}}
\par
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABDX}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABDX}
{
\pard\plain \s61\li360\sa60\sb30\qj\widctlpar\qj\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
\par
{
{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
Conversion gain to translate pitch value to stepper step counts. }}\par
{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
rad2step converts the balancing controller\'92s pitch correction into stepper microsteps, so the motors can execute the correction. This increment is added to the current left/right motor target position before calling {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAGQ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 StepperSetPos()}}}. Approximate theoretical value for 200 steps/rev and 1/16 microstepping: 200 * 16 / (2*pi) = 509,3. The implementation uses 520. \par
}}
