{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
Reads the accelerometer data from the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAHZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050}}} sensor, if enabled. }}\par
{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
@function mpuGetAcceleration\par
This function retrieves acceleration values along the X, Y, and Z axes from the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAHZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050}}} sensor, converts them to physical units in terms of g (gravitational acceleration), and stores them in the {\f2 accel_xyz}  array of the provided sensor instance. If the accelerometer is disabled, the function skips the I2C read and returns an error code.\par
{{\s5\sb90\sa30\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs16\cgrid 
Parameters\par}
\pard\plain \s81\li360\widctlpar\ql\adjustright \fs20\cgrid \trowd \trgaph108\trleft426\tblind426\trbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 \trbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 \trbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 \trbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 \trbrdrh\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 \trbrdrv\brdrs\brdrw10\brdrcf15 
