int16_t{
\par
\pard\plain {\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\afs24\lang1081\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af3\dbch\af3\loch\f8 \'01\u9642\tab}\ilvl2\ls1 \li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi-360\tx1080\li1080\ri0\lin1080\rin0\fi-360\kerning1\hich\af4\dbch\af5\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs20
Returns the result of the I2C transaction ({\f2 I2C_RETURN_CODE_t} ) if the accelerometer is enabled. A value of {\f2 I2C_SUCCESS}  (0) indicates successful data retrieval.\par
\pard\plain {\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\nowidctlpar\cf0\hich\af0\langfe2052\dbch\af0\afs24\lang1081\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \hich\af3\dbch\af3\loch\f8 \'01\u9642\tab}\ilvl2\ls1 \li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi-360\tx1080\li1080\ri0\lin1080\rin0\fi-360\kerning1\hich\af4\dbch\af5\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs20
Returns {\f2 1}  if the accelerometer is disabled ({\f2 accel_range}  set to {\f2 DISABLE} ).\par}
}}{
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab Checks if the accelerometer is enabled by verifying the {\f2 AccelRange}  parameter in the sensor instance. If disabled, the function immediately returns {\f2 1} .\par
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
2.\tab Reads 6 bytes of acceleration data from the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAHZ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MPU6050}}} registers via I2C communication.\par
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
3.\tab Combines the bytes to form 16-bit signed values representing the acceleration for each axis (X, Y, Z).\par
\pard\plain \s141\fi-360\li720\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
